Albuquerque police were searching for UFC light heavyweight champion Jon Jones handed himself in after a pregnant woman was injured in a hit-and-run accident on Sunday . 
  Police said the driver of a rented SUV jumped a red light and fled the scene . 
  The woman was hospitalised with a broken arm . 
  Witnesses said Jones ran from the scene but returned to grab 'a large handful of cash' from the car . 
  Police were seeking an arrest warrant for Jones on Monday . 
  However he turned himself in later the same day . 
  He would likely face a felony charge of leaving the scene of an accident . 
 